author: ETA PRIME
description:
We overclocked the AMD Ryzen AI MAX+ 395 and Radeon 8060S—AMD’s most powerful iGPU—to see if extra clocks actually move the needle. Using the Beelink GTR9, we pushed the CPU up to 5.3 GHz and the iGPU up to 3100 MHz. Power, temps, noise, and FPS… does it really make a difference? Let’s find out.
